@startuml Simulation_Practice

' ============================================
' SEQUENCE DIAGRAM: Simulation Practice Mode
' Bug Bounty and Its Simulation Platform
' ============================================

title Simulation Practice Mode - Sequence Diagram

actor "Researcher\n(Learner)" as Researcher
participant "Simulation Interface\n(Next.js)" as UI
participant "Simulation Engine\n(FastAPI)" as SimEngine
participant "Vulnerable App\n(OWASP Juice Shop)" as VulnApp
participant "Feedback Engine" as Feedback
participant "Simulation DB\n(Isolated)" as SimDB
participant "Notification Service" as Notification

== Access Simulation Environment ==
Researcher -> UI: Navigate to practice mode
UI -> SimEngine: GET /simulation/challenges
SimEngine -> SimDB: Query available challenges
SimDB --> SimEngine: Challenge list
SimEngine --> UI: Challenges (XSS, SQLi, CSRF, etc.)
UI --> Researcher: Display challenge categories

== Start Challenge ==
Researcher -> UI: Select "SQL Injection - Level 1"
UI -> SimEngine: POST /simulation/start\n{challenge_id: "sqli-001"}

SimEngine -> SimDB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
SimEngine -> SimDB: Create practice session
SimEngine -> SimDB: Initialize challenge state
SimDB --> SimEngine: Session ID: SIM-12345

SimEngine -> VulnApp: Deploy vulnerable instance
VulnApp --> SimEngine: Instance URL: http://sim-12345.local

SimEngine -> SimDB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
SimEngine --> UI: Session started\n{session_id, url, hints}
UI --> Researcher: "Challenge started!\nFind the SQL injection vulnerability"

== Practice & Exploration ==
Researcher -> VulnApp: Access vulnerable application
VulnApp --> Researcher: Login page displayed

Researcher -> VulnApp: Test input: ' OR '1'='1
VulnApp --> Researcher: SQL error message

Researcher -> UI: Request hint
UI -> SimEngine: GET /simulation/hint/SIM-12345
SimEngine -> SimDB: Check hint usage count
SimDB --> SimEngine: Hints used: 0/3
SimEngine --> UI: Hint: "Try manipulating the WHERE clause"
UI --> Researcher: Display hint

== Submit Vulnerability ==
Researcher -> VulnApp: Exploit: admin' --
VulnApp --> Researcher: Logged in as admin!

Researcher -> UI: Submit finding
UI -> SimEngine: POST /simulation/submit\n{session_id, exploit, description}

SimEngine -> Feedback: Validate submission
Feedback -> Feedback: Check exploit correctness
Feedback -> Feedback: Evaluate description quality
Feedback --> SimEngine: Score: 85/100\n{correctness: 90, description: 80}

SimEngine -> SimDB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
SimEngine -> SimDB: UPDATE session status = "completed"
SimEngine -> SimDB: INSERT score & feedback
SimEngine -> SimDB: UPDATE researcher progress
SimDB --> SimEngine: Progress: 15/50 challenges

SimEngine -> VulnApp: Terminate instance
VulnApp --> SimEngine: Instance stopped

SimEngine -> SimDB: COMMIT TRANSACTION

SimEngine --> UI: Challenge completed!\n{score: 85, feedback, next_challenge}
UI --> Researcher: "Great job! Score: 85/100\nFeedback: Good exploit, improve description"

== View Progress & Leaderboard ==
Researcher -> UI: View my progress
UI -> SimEngine: GET /simulation/progress
SimEngine -> SimDB: Query researcher stats
SimDB --> SimEngine: Stats: 15 completed, 850 points
SimEngine --> UI: Progress data
UI --> Researcher: Display progress dashboard

Researcher -> UI: View leaderboard
UI -> SimEngine: GET /simulation/leaderboard
SimEngine -> SimDB: Query top researchers
SimDB --> SimEngine: Top 10 list
SimEngine --> UI: Leaderboard
UI --> Researcher: Display rankings

== Unlock Advanced Challenges ==
alt Progress >= 20 challenges
    SimEngine -> SimDB: Check unlock criteria
    SimDB --> SimEngine: Criteria met
    SimEngine -> Notification: Send unlock notification
    Notification -> Researcher: Email: "Advanced challenges unlocked!"
    SimEngine --> UI: New challenges available
    UI --> Researcher: "You've unlocked Advanced level!"
end

@enduml